					<description><![CDATA[<p>Strategic Funding And Growing Institutional Confidence ROBOTERA has raised over USD 200 million in new funding. The round is led by SF Group with strong participation from financial and industrial</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/robotera-raises-over-200m-robotics-expansion/" data-wpel-link="internal">ROBOTERA Raises USD 200 Million To Scale Global Robotics Expansion</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Strategic Funding And Growing Institutional Confidence</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">ROBOTERA has raised over USD 200 million in new funding. The round is led by SF Group with strong participation from financial and industrial investors. Demand from investors exceeded the company’s initial target. The raise follows its RMB 1 billion strategic round completed in March.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Investor participation spans well-known global funds and major industrial partners. The list includes HSG, IDG Capital, Hillhouse Investment, CICC Capital, Jingming Capital, SparkEdge Capital, Luxin Venture Capital Group, Unite Pioneers Capital, Longqi Investment and several corporate investment groups. Existing backers increased their positions. This reflects rising confidence in ROBOTERA’s technology and commercial execution.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company reports significant progress in reaching product-market fit. It has deployed its systems across more than ten logistics centres. These deployments include large facilities operated by national logistics companies. This has strengthened its position in embodied intelligence. Recent delivery volumes have also accelerated. The company began thousand-unit shipments in Q2 2026 with growth above 300%.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The round brings together a broad coalition of institutional and industrial partners. Many of these partners plan to support commercial rollouts. They also provide real-world scenarios for deployment. This helps ROBOTERA refine performance through continuous field feedback.</span></p>
<h2><b>Robotics Hardware System And Technical Foundations</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">ROBOTERA has built a fully in-house robotics hardware system. More than 95% of core components are developed internally. This includes actuation systems and full humanoid platforms. The company highlights that internal development provides greater control over quality. It also improves performance in real-world environments.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">A central feature of its hardware system is its full direct-drive dexterous hand architecture. It is the first in the sector to adopt this design at scale. The design delivers precision, adaptability, and durability. These qualities are essential for logistics and industrial tasks. Long-term deployment has validated the hand’s reliability.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company develops hardware with a clear focus on mobility and manipulation. This combines advanced motion control with next-generation robotics structures. The system is optimised for difficult warehouse and manufacturing tasks. These tasks require accuracy, safety and consistent long-term performance.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">ROBOTERA’s hardware is supported by continuous software refinement. The system collects data during active deployments. This data informs ongoing updates to control systems. It also helps improve environmental awareness and task efficiency. The combined approach strengthens real-world adaptability.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The robotics company offers several humanoid models. These include a full-size bipedal unit, field-tested </span><a href="https://dictionary.cambridge.org/dictionary/english/humanoid" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">humanoids</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for extreme conditions, and an embodied AI model designed for complex reasoning tasks. Precision hands support logistics and industrial workflows. These hands are designed for near-human effectiveness.</span></p>
<h2><b>Enterprise Adoption And Real-World Deployment Growth<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_200909" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200909" class="size-full wp-image-200909" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/a-photograph-of-sleek-humanoid-robots-bu_AkrEJyEoVw6JjXlnksiccw_BQFpPWCVTiSTcuKo0GR36w_cover.png" alt="Humanoid robots performing logistics, manufacturing, and service tasks with AI-driven precision and continuous learning." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-200909" class="wp-caption-text">ROBOTERA expands real-world deployment of humanoid robotics, delivering scalable, high-precision automation across industries. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">ROBOTERA’s technology has been adopted by major global technology companies and research institutions. Adoption spans robotics research, AI development and advanced manufacturing. These organisations use the system for mobility, manipulation and testing. This reflects the platform’s maturity across demanding environments.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company has established strong partnerships in logistics. Deployments across large distribution centres have validated performance at scale. Facilities have used its humanoids for sorting, transport and handling. These tasks require precision in fast-paced environments. Feedback has strengthened overall system performance.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">ROBOTERA continues to expand into new industries. These include automotive manufacturing, electronics production and service operations. Each sector benefits from embodied intelligence in different ways. Automotive plants can automate repetitive mobility tasks. Electronics manufacturers can improve high-precision handling. Service environments use the systems for steady operational support.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Investors see these industry expansions as indicators of long-term potential. Industrial operators provide large deployment opportunities. They also provide structured environments suited to robotics. These factors support rapid commercial adoption. ROBOTERA expects growth to accelerate over the next year.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company’s expansion strategy focuses on performance reliability. It integrates field data into product updates. This ensures that deployments improve over time. It also helps the company respond quickly to customer needs. Reliable iteration is a core requirement for large-scale adoption.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/kalshi-raises-1b-series-f-prediction-market-growth/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Kalshi Raises $1B Series F To Scale Prediction Market Platform</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Scaling Commercialisation Across Global Markets</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">ROBOTERA is entering a phase of rapid commercialisation. Strong funding enables operational expansion. The company plans to scale production capacity. It will also invest in engineering to support next-generation models. This will help it meet rising demand across global markets.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company expects large orders from logistics and manufacturing sectors. These industries seek automation to reduce costs and improve efficiency. Humanoid robotics provide flexible support across many tasks. ROBOTERA’s systems are positioned to capture this demand.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Its strategic investors support practical deployment paths. Industrial groups offer sizeable test environments. They also offer commercial opportunities for scaled rollouts. Collaborative development across partners strengthens long-term adoption.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company aims to position itself as a global leader in embodied intelligence. Its hardware system forms the technical foundation. Its field-tested deployments demonstrate commercial readiness. Rising investor commitment supports its long-term expansion.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">ROBOTERA plans further global partnerships in manufacturing and automation. These partnerships help create new deployment categories. They also support entry into new regions. The company is focused on strengthening its position in the global robotics ecosystem.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/robotera-raises-over-200m-robotics-expansion/" data-wpel-link="internal">ROBOTERA Raises USD 200 Million To Scale Global Robotics Expansion</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
