					<description><![CDATA[<p>Fazeshift, a developer of AI-native software that automates complex financial workflows, has announced a $17M Series A. This new tranche, led by F.Prime Capital, raises the company&#8217;s total funding to</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/fazeshift-raises-17m-to-transform-autonomous-finance/" data-wpel-link="internal">Fazeshift Raises $17M to Transform Autonomous Finance</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://www.fazeshift.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Fazeshift</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, a developer of AI-native software that automates complex financial workflows, has announced a $17M Series A. This new tranche, led by F.Prime Capital, raises the company&#8217;s total funding to $22M and is a turning point for how enterprise finance teams will operate their most time-consuming workflows.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/quantum-motion-raises-160-million-for-quantum-growth/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">round </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">was further joined by leading institutional investors like Gradient Ventures (Google’s AI-focused seed fund), Y Combinator, Wayfinder Ventures, Pioneer Fund, and Ritual Capital. Fazeshift&#8217;s new round comes as the company reveals a 12x growth in revenue over the last year and only emphasizes their findings that there is a demand for &#8220;autonomous agents&#8221; to come in and perform end-to-end business workflows rather than simply recommending what task to do next.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">From &#8220;Co-Pilot&#8221; to &#8220;Co-Worker&#8221;</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Fazeshift is based in San Francisco and was co-founded in 2023 by former BCG consultant and mechanical engineer Caitlin Leksana (CEO) and MIT-trained nuclear submarine officer Timmy Galvin (CTO). The founders set out to battle the disconnected state of the huge and growing world of financial software, which, despite all of the ERPs and CRMs, has not solved the connective tissue of finance, which is matching payments, chasing late invoices, and reconciling data from multiple disparate sources.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_200904" style="width: 490px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200904" class="size-full wp-image-200904" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Fazeshift.jpg" alt="Fazeshift" width="480" height="48" /><p id="caption-attachment-200904" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Fazeshift</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Fazeshift&#8217;s platform puts on top of your existing software stack or banks, portals, netsuite or other systems an intelligent control layer which directs autonomous agents to accomplish complex and varied tasks without requiring a &#8220;human in the loop&#8221; for each step. Unlike all other automation platforms that are rules-based and require a lot of programming, Fazeshift&#8217;s agents are contextually aware and autonomous; they will do everything but toast your bread.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/quantum-motion-raises-160-million-for-quantum-growth/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Quantum Motion Raises $160 Million for Quantum Growth</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Driving Tangible Financial Outcomes</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company’s initial focus is on accounts receivable (AR), a sector traditionally bogged down by manual follow-ups and data entry. According to company data, Fazeshift is currently automating over 90% of manual AR tasks for its client base. The impact has been immediate for its customers, which include high-growth &#8220;unicorns&#8221; and established public entities such as Sigma Computing, Snyk, Meter, and Clipboard Health.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">One early deployment saw the platform process over 9,000 unique customer communications in a single day, leading to the recovery of $7.4 million in cash within just weeks of implementation. This level of efficiency is particularly critical for industries with complex, fragmented payment cycles, such as wholesale distribution, construction, and HVAC services.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Roadmap Toward Autonomous Finance</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The new $17M capital raise is being used to aggressively develop products and expand into the market. While accounts receivable is the initial product, the company has a longer-term strategy of building an autonomous CFO suite of tools by extending agent functionality into accounts payable, treasury and FP&amp;A.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As AI evolves from a creative assistant into what can be a coworker, Fazeshift is seeking to be at the head of the pack. By handing off execution to AI agents, the company wants to take humans out of clerical data entry and enable a focus on governance and strategy.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/fazeshift-raises-17m-to-transform-autonomous-finance/" data-wpel-link="internal">Fazeshift Raises $17M to Transform Autonomous Finance</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
