		<link>https://ventureburn.com/balcony-secures-12-7m-for-avalanche-asset-growth/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Fri, 08 May 2026 10:22:33 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=200899</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Property intelligence firm Balcony revealed that it has secured $12.7 million in seed funding. The funding was led by Blockchange Ventures and included multiple strategic investors as part of the</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/balcony-secures-12-7m-for-avalanche-asset-growth/" data-wpel-link="internal">Balcony Secures $12.7M for Avalanche Asset Growth</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Property intelligence firm </span><a href="https://balcony.technology/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Balcony </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">revealed that it has secured $12.7 million in seed </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/quantum-motion-raises-160-million-for-quantum-growth/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">. The funding was led by Blockchange Ventures and included multiple strategic investors as part of the round. Today’s funding increases the property intelligence firm’s total funding to $14 million and will be used for building RWA infrastructure on the Avalanche protocol.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Founded in 2021, Balcony has positioned itself as the &#8220;digital rails&#8221; for the U.S. property market. The company’s flagship platform, Keystone, provides a unified intelligence layer that integrates directly with existing county land record systems. By transforming fragmented, centuries-old physical and digital records into structured, verifiable data, Balcony aims to eliminate the friction that has historically plagued the $400 billion real estate transaction market.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Rebuilding the Foundation of Property Ownership</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The U.S. real estate market relies on more than 3,000 individual county offices to maintain land records. This decentralized and often antiquated system has become a growing target for title fraud and a bottleneck for capital markets. </span>Balcony&#8217;s approach does not seek to replace governmental systems but to work alongside them. It creates a secure, blockchain-backed registry offering a &#8220;360-degree view&#8221; of every property parcel.</p>
<div id="attachment_200901" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200901" class="wp-image-200901 size-large" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Balcony-1024x1024.jpg" alt="Balcony" width="1024" height="1024" /><p id="caption-attachment-200901" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Balcony</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">“Property ownership is a pillar of our economy, and in today’s world, it’s also a matter of national security,” said Ken Seiff, managing partner at Blockchange Ventures. “Our fragmented system is vulnerable. Balcony’s unique ability to create a verifiable view of land records is a game-changer, empowering governments to protect against fraud and monitor foreign ownership.”</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The choice of the Avalanche blockchain is strategic. Avalanche’s &#8220;Subnet&#8221; technology allows for high-throughput, customizable environments that meet the strict regulatory and compliance requirements of government agencies. By utilizing Avalanche, Balcony provides a permanent, immutable ledger that can power everything from title insurance to secondary market trading of tokenized real estate assets.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/quantum-motion-raises-160-million-for-quantum-growth/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Quantum Motion Raises $160 Million for Quantum Growth</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Proven Success in the Public Sector</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Balcony is already proving its utility at scale. The company recently signed a landmark five-year contract with Bergen County, New Jersey, to digitize and manage 370,000 property parcels representing approximately $240 billion in real estate value. Other early adopters include Hopkins County, Kentucky, which is utilizing Keystone to unify land records and tax assessment data.</span></p>
<p>&#8220;Modernizing how land records are organized and accessed is critical for counties like ours,&#8221; said John Hogan. &#8220;Balcony&#8217;s platform helps us organize decades of records, improving transparency and access for our office and the public.&#8221;</p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Scaling for a Tokenized Future</span></h2>
<p>The new capital will expand Balcony&#8217;s engineering and go-to-market teams to partner with governments nationwide. Balcony&#8217;s infrastructure supports real-world asset lifecycles, including issuance, investor management, and compliance for tokenized securities. As assets move on-chain, Balcony&#8217;s digital rails give mortgage lenders, title insurers, and institutional investors speed and certainty.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/balcony-secures-12-7m-for-avalanche-asset-growth/" data-wpel-link="internal">Balcony Secures $12.7M for Avalanche Asset Growth</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
